50|$|Biologists {{have been}} rearing the June sucker in Red Butte Reservoir, and more {{recently}} in the Springville, Utah fish hatchery which had been closed due to an outbreak of <b>whirling</b> <b>disease.</b> As <b>whirling</b> <b>disease</b> does not affect June sucker, the hatchery was reopened to house the June sucker. After the June sucker grow to a certain size, they are released into Utah Lake to help build the population.|$|E
