5000|$|Threats to Wyoming {{game fish}} include the New Zealand mud snail, the common carp, and <b>whirling</b> <b>disease.</b> In addition, the {{introduction}} of brook sticklebacks (Culaea incontans), walleyes, ling suckers, and white suckers have impacted the ecology of native game fish. Conservation efforts to protect Wyoming game fish include licensing, creel limits, and issuing conservation stamps.|$|E
